# SKAdTestError.Code.invalidSourceIdentifier

**Case**

The postback’s identifier isn’t two, three, or four digits.

## Declaration

```swift
case invalidSourceIdentifier
```

## Discussion

A valid postback includes two to four digits of the impression’s [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/StoreKit/SKAdImpression/sourceIdentifier]. For more information about the varying length of source identifiers, see [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/StoreKit/receiving-postbacks-in-multiple-conversion-windows].

## Other Errors

- **SKAdTestError.Code.invalidVersion**: A postback contains an incorrect version number.
- **SKAdTestError.Code.invalidImpressionId**: The impression ID isn’t a valid UUID string.
- **SKAdTestError.Code.invalidSourceAppAdamId**: The app ID is less than zero.
- **SKAdTestError.Code.invalidSourceDomain**: The source domain isn’t in the correct format.
- **SKAdTestError.Code.unknownError**: An unknown error occurred in the testing environment.
